  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dd2\u0dbb \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd2\u0db1\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dbd\u0db6\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The permanent cabinet next week",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to government sources, a new cabinet will be appointed next week to replace the currently appointed temporary cabinet.",
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe has discussed with all political parties regarding the formation of an all-party government, but since no final agreement has been reached regarding the all-party government, it is known that the new cabinet is likely to be appointed under an all-party system.",
        "It is learned that during the appointment of this cabinet, the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna has also submitted a list of district leaders who should be given cabinet ministerships to the President.",
        "It is also known that the names of Dr. Ramesh Pathirana, Prasanna Ranatunga, Janaka Bandara Thennakoon, Johnston Fernando, Rohitha Abeygunawardena, CB Ratnayake, Pavitra Vanniarachchi, SM Chandrasena, Namal Rajapaksa, Dr. Bandula Gunawardena, Sanath Nishantha, Kanchana Wijesekara have been included in it. .",
        "It has been learned that several members of Samagi Balawega are to be included in the new cabinet, Jeevan Thondaman of Sri Lanka Labor Congress and ALM Athaullah, leader of National Congress, are also to be appointed ministers.",
        "It is learned that if it is not possible to form an all-party government, the government is also discussing the formation of a national government."
      ],
